SIMPLE: scutcheon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scutcheon
<hw>Scutch"eon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Aphetic form of
<ets>escutcheon</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An escutcheon; an
emblazoned shield.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The corpse lay in state, with all the pomp of
<qex>scutcheons</qex>, wax lights, black hangings, and mutes.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small plate of metal, as the shield around a
keyhole. See <er>Escutcheon</er>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scutcheoned</ent>⟦br⟧
